 in ordinary representation is found as well. The possible\ngeneralizations of considered Lie algebras to the arbitrary dimensional SO(n)\nand SO(m,n) are discussed briefly.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 17 Oct 2021 12:41:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 19 Feb 2023 19:48:39 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 30 May 2023 05:21:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-31"}
